  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n0.2.0\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge coverage\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nIn a setup similar to this-\r\n<img width=\"409\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/56924144/68923c6f-cbf5-4c03-b4c3-df61eff5669b\">\r\nwhere 2 contracts inherit the same interface and implement the same functions and have the same source layout, although they are both tested fully, `forge coverage` fails to recognise hits on one of the contracts. \r\nIn this case it would fail to recognise hits on `SecondContract` as `FirstContract` comes first alphabetically.\r\n\r\nI confirmed this by changing their names to ensure it picked up the alphabetically first contract and also confirmed that when the source layout of either contracts is changed, `forge coverage` manages to recognise all hits on both of them.",
